            <title><![CDATA[Researchers are sounding the alarm on a little-known risk of connected cars]]></title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;Get ready for the worst traffic jam of your life. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&amp;#x2019;re driving down Fifth Avenue in Manhattan, and all of a sudden your car breaks on its own. A hacker has managed to attack your car through your internet-connected entertainment system and has &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2016/8/2/12353186/car-hack-jeep-cherokee-vulnerability-miller-valasek"&gt;seized control of the brakes&lt;/a&gt;, bringing you to a halt. The gas pedal isn&amp;#x2019;t working, so you&amp;#x2019;re stuck.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/90383517/researchers-are-sounding-the-alarm-on-a-little-known-risk-of-connected-cars?partner=rss&amp;amp;utm_source=feedburner&amp;amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=feedburner+fastcompany&amp;amp;utm_content=feedburner"&gt;Read Full Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/fastcodesign/feed/~4/NzEqZ5gcwXI" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
