            <title><![CDATA[Legendary type foundry Monotype sold to private equity for $825 million]]></title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;The 132-year-old company commissioned many of history&amp;#x2019;s most recognizable fonts, including Gill Sans, Arial, and Times New Roman. Now it&amp;#x2019;s in the hands of a private equity firm. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/company/monotype"&gt;Monotype Imaging&lt;/a&gt;, the publicly traded type foundry behind some of the world&amp;#x2019;s most iconic fonts, is being sold. Palo Alto, California-based private equity firm HGGC plans to&amp;#xA0;&lt;a href="http://www.typeroom.eu/scanner?page=0&amp;amp;nid=1457"&gt;acquire all Monotype&amp;#x2019;s stock&lt;/a&gt; for $19.85 a share, or about $825 million, and Monotype will no longer be listed on any public exchanges.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.fastcompany.com/90382770/legendary-type-foundry-monotype-sold-to-private-equity-for-825-million?partner=rss&amp;amp;utm_source=feedburner&amp;amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;amp;utm_campaign=feedburner+fastcompany&amp;amp;utm_content=feedburner"&gt;Read Full Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/fastcodesign/feed/~4/cvrZ75JUoz0" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
